node.text:
This is the most incredible way to fry an #eggplant!

INGREDIENTS
Eggplants
Salt
Water
Tapioca flour
Oil

METHOD
Peel an eggplant. Cut into large chunks.
Form a grid on each piece without cutting it all together.
Add salt to a bowl with water and place each piece of eggplant and wait for 20 minutes.
Cover each piece with flour. Deep fry with very hot oil.
Serve with sour cream.

node.title: Fried eggplants: a perfect side dish for a special dinner!

node.text:
A simple method to make amazing fluffy #bread!

INGREDIENTS
400ml (1 3/4 cup) Milk
7g dry yeast
2 tbsp sugar
600g (4 cups) Flour
1 tsp salt
30ml (2 1/4 tbsp) Oil
Butter
Apricot jam

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 40 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 pieces.
Boil in hot water for 3 minutes from both sides.
Transfer to the baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 200’C(390’F).
Serve with butter and jam.

node.text:
Kids will love these amazing bi-color #muffins: easy and fluffy! 
 
INGREDIENTS
1 egg
50g sugar
8g vanilla sugar
60ml oil
100ml milk
160g flour
8g baking powder
1 tbsp cacao powder
3 tbsp milk
Almond slices

METHOD
Pour an egg into a bowl, add sugar, vanilla sugar and mix well.
Add oil, milk and mix well.
Mix flour with baking powder and pour into the previous mixture.
Mix cocoa and milk in another bowl. Add half of the mixture to get two different colors.
Pour a little of each mixture into each hole of a muffin tray to make two-color muffins and add almond slices.
Bake for 25 minutes at 180°C (356°F).

node.text:
Beautiful and delicious, these #crepes are just amazing! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
100g (3/4 cup) Flour
230ml (1 cup) water
1 tbsp olive oil
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
8-10 zucchini Flowers
150g baked ham
100g mozzarella cheese

METHOD
In a bowl mix together eggs with salt, pepper, flour, water, oil.
Make pancakes onto the prepared pan and put the flower on top. Fry from both sides.
Fill with baked ham slices and mozzarella slices.

node.text:
The recipe to make amazing #crepes every time!

INGREDIENTS
3 eggs
2g (½ tsp) salt
10g (2 tsp) sugar
125g (1 cup) flour
250ml (1 cup) milk
12ml (1 tbsp) oil
 
Filling:
Honey
Coconut grains
 
METHOD
Add eggs, sugar, salt to the mixing bowl. Whisk with a mixer.
Add milk, oil, and sifted flour. Mix. Rest for 30 minutes.
Bake on an oiled pan.
Serve with coconut grains and honey.

node.text:
These #hashbrowns will be gone in SECONDS!

INGREDIENTS
3 potatoes
1 egg
12g (2 tbsp) cornstarch
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) garlic powder
oil
 
METHOD
Boil the potatoes for 8-10 minutes. Grate the potatoes.
Add egg, starch, salt, and garlic. Mix.
Shape fritters and place them in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Fry in hot oil. Serve.

node.text:
You have never tried an #omelet this tasty!

INGREDIENTS
Red bell pepper
Yellow bell pepper
6 eggs
50g parmesan
Chives
Garlic
Thyme
Extra virgin olive oil
Salt
Pepper
Butter

METHOD
Add minced garlic and oil to a pan. Sprinkle over dried thyme. Cut the peppers, add to the pan, and cook. Then add chives
Pour 6 eggs into a bowl, add Parmesan cheese and mix thoroughly
Add the pepper mixture to the bowl with the egg and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a pan and cook on both sides to get an omelet.

node.text:
This #chocolatepudding is so creamy and irresistible!

INGREDIENTS
1l (4 cups) milk
2 egg yolks
1 cup flour
1 cup sugar
2 tbsp cocoa powder
1 tbsp butter
1 tsp vanilla sugar
1/2 cup chocolate
240ml (1 cup) water
Biscuits
 
METHOD
Into the pan add egg yolks, flour, cocoa powder, sugar, and milk, cook on low heat until thick. Add in butter, chocolate, and vanilla extract. Turn off the heat and pour in water.
Layout biscuits on the bottom of each plate. Cover them with prepared chocolate mixture, and repeat it again. Refrigerate for 1 hour, sprinkle with more chocolate chips.

node.text:
Just eggs, veggies and a muffin pan to make an incredible dinner! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
Butter
1 onion
Garlic
Carrots
Red pepper
Leeks
4 eggs
80ml (1/3 cup) milk
Parmesan
Salt
Black pepper
Extra virgin olive oil
 
METHOD
Melt the butter in a frying pan. Then add grated garlic, carrot, onion, red pepper, leek, salt, pepper, and mix. Put in a bowl once cooked.
Mix the eggs and milk in a bowl, add salt and pepper, then add the cooked vegetables and mix well.
Brush some oil over the muffin tray then pour in the egg mixture. Cook for 15 minutes at 200ºC (392ºF).

This idea is so cute, perfect to surprise everyone with a few basic ingredients! 

INGREDIENTS
320g (2.5 cups) flour
3 tbsp sugar
1/2 tsp salt
7g dry yeast
190ml (3/4 cup) warm milk
1 egg
1 egg yolk
3 tbsp soft butter
Salami slices
Cheese slices

METHOD
Mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add in the egg and soft butter, mix everything well and let the dough rise for about 2 hours.
Roll out the dough cut into strips, top with salami and cheese.
Wrap them and spread with egg yolk. Bake at 180°C (350°F) for 40 minutes.

node.text:
The whole family will love this buns for dinner! 
 
INGREDIENTS
250ml (1 cup) warm milk
1 large egg
50g (1/4 cup) yogurt
50g (1/4 cup) sugar
400g (3 1/4 cup) flour
7g dry yeast
4g (1 tsp) salt
60g (1/4 cup) butter
Butter for filling
 
Egg wash:
1 egg
20ml (2 tbsp) milk
Salt
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl, add warm milk, egg, and sugar. Mix well. Add flour, yeast, and salt. Mix. Rest for 20 minutes.
Add the butter and mix. Knead and fold the dough until smooth. When it's smooth, place in an oiled bowl and rest for 60 minutes.
Deflate the dough by punching out the gas. Flatten out the dough and divide it into 16 pieces. Round each into a ball. Rest for 20 minutes.
Flatten the dough upside down. Fill with butter. Pinch the seams to seal.
Place in a greased baking dish. Cover for 20 minutes.
Brush with egg wash. Top with salt.
Bake at 360F/180C for 18-20 minutes. Brush with melted butter. Serve.

node.text:
These savory #croissants are a must-try! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Dough:
500g flour
70g melted butter
7g dry yeast
10g salt
40g sugar
300ml milk
 
Filling:
Salami
Mozzarella cheese
 
Coat:
Sesame seeds
Egg
Milk

METHOD
Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl. Add the yeast to warm milk, then pour over the flour. Add melted butter and mix very well.
Let rise for 4 hours.
Cut the dough into two large pieces. Roll out one piece into a circle, then cut into 8 even triangle slices. Place salami and cheese on each piece. Roll from the largest edge to form a croissant.
Place them on a baking sheet and rest for 1 hour.
Mix egg and milk and cover each croissant. Sprinkle sesame seeds on each one. Bake for 20 minutes at 225°C (437 °F).

node.text:
This is the most incredible way to fry an #eggplant!

INGREDIENTS
Eggplants
Salt
Water
Tapioca flour
Oil

METHOD
Peel an eggplant. Cut into large chunks.
Form a grid on each piece without cutting it all together.
Add salt to a bowl with water and place each piece of eggplant and wait for 20 minutes.
Cover each piece with flour. Deep fry with very hot oil.
Serve with sour cream.

node.text:
A simple method to make amazing fluffy #bread!

INGREDIENTS
400ml (1 3/4 cup) Milk
7g dry yeast
2 tbsp sugar
600g (4 cups) Flour
1 tsp salt
30ml (2 1/4 tbsp) Oil
Butter
Apricot jam

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 40 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 pieces.
Boil in hot water for 3 minutes from both sides.
Transfer to the baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 200’C(390’F).
Serve with butter and jam.

node.text:
Kids will love these amazing bi-color #muffins: easy and fluffy! 
 
INGREDIENTS
1 egg
50g sugar
8g vanilla sugar
60ml oil
100ml milk
160g flour
8g baking powder
1 tbsp cacao powder
3 tbsp milk
Almond slices

METHOD
Pour an egg into a bowl, add sugar, vanilla sugar and mix well.
Add oil, milk and mix well.
Mix flour with baking powder and pour into the previous mixture.
Mix cocoa and milk in another bowl. Add half of the mixture to get two different colors.
Pour a little of each mixture into each hole of a muffin tray to make two-color muffins and add almond slices.
Bake for 25 minutes at 180°C (356°F).

Beautiful and delicious, these #crepes are just amazing! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
100g (3/4 cup) Flour
230ml (1 cup) water
1 tbsp olive oil
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
8-10 zucchini Flowers
150g baked ham
100g mozzarella cheese

METHOD
In a bowl mix together eggs with salt, pepper, flour, water, oil.
Make pancakes onto the prepared pan and put the flower on top. Fry from both sides.
Fill with baked ham slices and mozzarella slices.

node.text: Just potatoes, parmesan, and flour! They will be a hit! 😍INGREDIENTS600g potatoes100g parmesan cheesesaltpepper2 tbsp olive oil250g flour hamcheese METHOD1. Boil the potatoes or cook them in the microwave for about 10 minutes. Mash the potatoes and add the flour, and the Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.2. Spread out the mixture on a sheet of parchment paper and cut out some circles. 3. Place cheese and ham on one circle and make a calzone.4. Pour some olive oil in a pan and cook each calzone for 5 minutes on each side.5. Your potato calzone is ready to serve!#cookistwow #cookistrecipe #recipes #cooking #food #foodie #instafood #foodlove #italianfood #yummy #dinner #lunch #food #yummy #instafood ##homemade #foodstagram #eat #instacake #instaphone #foodblogger #foodblog #Iovefood #instamood #instagood #bestoftheday #picoftheday

node.text:
Stop making chicken the usual way!
Try this recipe, it's outsatnding 😋

INGREDIENTS 

Chicken breasts 1lb. (450g)
Salt and pepper, to taste
Balsamic vinegar 1 tbsp (15ml)
Worcestershire sauce ½ tbsp (8ml)
Garlic powder 1 tsp (4g)
Eggs 3 
Bread 6 slices, crust-free, center diced
Oil, for frying

METHOD

Cut the chicken into bite-size pieces.

Place the chicken into a bowl.

Drizzle the balsamic vinegar, sauce, and garlic powder over the chicken.

Beat one egg and pour over the chicken.

Season the chicken with salt and stir to combine.

Beat two remaining eggs in a bowl.

Place the flour in a separate bowl or plate, and diced bread into a third bowl or plate.

Dip the chicken into the flour, then eggs, and finally coat with the bread.

Heat 2-inches (4cm) of oil in a skillet.

Fry the chicken until golden on all sides.

Drain on paper towels and serve.

Serve with ketchup or hot sauce and enjoy ❤

The recipe to make amazing #crepes every time!

INGREDIENTS
3 eggs
2g (½ tsp) salt
10g (2 tsp) sugar
125g (1 cup) flour
250ml (1 cup) milk
12ml (1 tbsp) oil
 
Filling:
Honey
Coconut grains
 
METHOD
Add eggs, sugar, salt to the mixing bowl. Whisk with a mixer.
Add milk, oil, and sifted flour. Mix. Rest for 30 minutes.
Bake on an oiled pan.
Serve with coconut grains and honey.
